Members of the public who went to the licencing departments in Nelspruit said they were told there were problems with the system and they couldn&#8217;t be assisted. Lowvelder has received several calls and messages who visited the licensing department and could not be assisted.According to the reports received, the following licencing offices are currently close: Mbombela Riverside Mbombela Civic White River HazyviewIt is not the first time that the municipality couldn&#8217;t render these services as they also closed in July due to what it called an administrative challenge. There was no papers to do licence renewals.The municipality&#8217;s spokesman, Mr Joseph Ngala, was not available to respond to the queries. More information will be published as it becomes available.